# Scene Persistence Context

You are touching scene-level persistence (world item transforms, scene placement restore, scene transition persistence).
For general world layout edits in `Bootstrap`/`MainTown`/`IndoorRangeInstance` (and compatibility scenes) that are not persistence-focused, use the world/vehicles router instead.

Convention:
- Place scene/world-item save-restore orchestration scripts under `Reloader/Assets/_Project/Core/Scripts/Persistence/**`.
- Keep persistence-oriented class names discoverable with `*Persistence*` naming where practical.

Read these docs:

1. `docs/design/core-architecture.md` — shared patterns and scene/runtime boundaries
2. `docs/design/save-contract-quick-reference.md` — ID ownership and location mapping rules
3. `docs/design/save-and-progression.md` — exact-restore contract
4. `docs/design/world-and-vehicles.md` — scene/layout expectations when world or travel flows are involved
5. `docs/design/world-scene-contracts.md` — scene wiring and validation gates
6. `docs/design/extensible-development-contracts.md` — cross-domain persistence/integration guardrails

Do not load unrelated deep domain docs unless the task crosses that system boundary.
